# Goal
Reduce migration diff from the local demo-app DSL surface to the current mainline `libs/sdk-dsl` without regressing runtime-correct behavior.

# Source priority
1. Current mainline runtime-correct `libs/sdk-dsl`
2. `docs/ts-dsl-sdk/final-dsl-sdk-mapping-reference.md`
3. `docs/ts-dsl-sdk/complex-flow-materialization-reference.md`
4. `references/demo-app-main/**` only as a compatibility donor/reference

# Key principles
- Prefer thin aliases/wrappers over behavioral rewrites.
- Do not reintroduce old runtime assumptions from demo app.
- Do not widen scope into transport/API client concerns.
- `requestBackwardPayment(...)` remains deferred/runtime-guarded.
- If a helper already exists semantically, add a compatibility alias instead of duplicating logic.

# Required helper families
- serialization/export compatibility helpers
- document marker/link/anchor wrappers
- AI alias helpers
- MyOS permission builder
- MyOS subscribe-with-matchers helper

# Must not do
- Do not replace the mainline SDK with demo-app code wholesale.
- Do not regress canonical scenarios.
- Do not add private-provenance references.
- Do not change final mappings only to preserve old syntax.
